entry.et: Middle English egge, from Old Norse egg; akin to Old English ǣg egg, Latin ovum, Greek ōion

def.dt: :the hard-shelled reproductive body produced by a bird and especially by the common domestic chicken
:an animal reproductive body consisting of an ovum together with its nutritive and protective envelopes and having the capacity to develop into a new individual capable of independent existence

:a protective case enclosing eggs :ootheca called also egg capsule
